description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic Registered Mental Health nurse to join our friendly Community Mental Health Team based at Brookheys in Altrincham.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post provides a challenging opportunity to work within an established fully integrated and supportive team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will hold and manage a caseload of service users who require care coordination under the Care Programme Approach. By assessing your clients and carers needs you will be able to access and sign post to a wide range of community resources and provider services available in Trafford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for the running of the weekly depot clinic, managing the booking system, ordering depot medication and liaising with other care coordinators and medical staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will receive regular clinical and managerial supervision and developmental appraisal thus enhancing your current practice and future career prospects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If potential candidates would like to take up the opportunity of an informal chat prior to applying for the post, please contact the team manager – details provided below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLinda SkinnionJob titleTeam ManagerEmail addresslinda.skinnion@gmmh.nhs.ukTelephone number0161 357 1340&lt;/p&gt;
